event.doc_name: Complaint for Declaratory and Injunctive Relief

evidence.text: Plaintiffs filed suit under the Administrative Procedure Act ("APA") seeking to prevent Defendants from implementing changes to federal regulations enforcing the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act (the "ACA,", or the "Act").
evidence.source_document: Complaint for Declaratory and Injunctive Relief

evidence.text: Plaintiffs' motion for a stay under 5 U.S.C. § 705 or, in the alternative, for a preliminary injunction, ECF 11, construed as a motion for a stay under 5 U.S.C. § 705, is GRANTED in part and DENIED in part
The Court finds that Plaintiffs have met their burden of showing that there is a strong likelihood that they will succeed on the merits of their challenges to seven provisions of the Rule.
